With a dance of fog, a twirl of mist, the dreaming cocoon rests all around.
---
The fog comes as natures gentle hand to once more give nature a chance to return into view after her graceful repose.
---
There are days the world comes to full colour from the night, from the greys under the moon to every colour of the rainbow and more. Today we have the fog, and so as it warms up the world will be born from this whiteness, as if it were art appearing on a three dimensional canvass.
---
The fog comes as softest white to embrace all, to make it a cocoon until the heat returns and the colours of nature are ready to flutter once more.
---
When the world becomes a new brilliant white page, as if nine clouds had kissed the earth, the fog only awaits the sun to unveil the scene upon its own perfect timing.
---
Today the clouds sit upon the earth, as if they decided the heavens were down here instead. So I walk on the grass, flying as high as the birds, seeing only white.
---
The trees are veiled in the lightest of mists, their trunks sombre brown with sable cracks that gnarl the bark. As my eye travels to the edge of the woodland they become silhouettes against a blanket of white, as if it is only daylight where I stand, as if I am encircled by twilight.
---
In the fog the city is blurred like an old painting; it could be a great work drawn by expert hand. The buildings and the Japanese cherry trees are silhouetted black, two-dimensional. The streets yawn in every direction with only the old newspaper dispensers and street-lamps to break the view between buildings so high that the tops disappear in the swirling white.
---
An aching mist of aeon’s beauty hugged the lighthouse of white and red. Chill in ethereal repose ‘twas a constellation of water-motes, motes that floated in the breeze, floated with angelic ease.
---
Rain blossomed from the ether as desert flowers to quenched sand, appearing independent of both clouds and gravity. From whence it had come, I failed to fathom.
---
There was a gentleness to the early mist, as if by removing the precise edges of the land it invited night's dreamy bliss to linger.
---
In that day of gentle mist the blue river became new-lamb white.
---
The mist came as cocoon to the springtime wands and buds.
---
The mist danced upon the lake waters as if it were in some magical daydream.
---
And from the mist that hugged the earth, a comforting blanket that moved as serene water, there came bold purple petals of perfect form.
---
In the mist my anticipation grew to see the meadows and sky once more, for their bright hues to begin their daytime shine.
---
The air that night was bath and soap, something about it left you feeling warm and clean.
---
At the kiss of night the air took on a welcoming soothing quality.
---
The sea-brine air brought with it the levity of the birds.
---
In the woodland, the loamy air had a way of cocooning the soul and inviting butterfly wings to grow.
---
Bathed in the starlit black the air refreshed my soul as if my reboot button had been hit.
---
There is a kind of spring fragranced air that grows wings on angel kin.
---
The air on that planet had a rainbow swirl, as if bright inks were dropped into a current with precision. On the skin it felt as silk on a hot day, cool and smooth.
---
There was a freshness to the air that invited the feet to run and jump.
---
She inhaled the air as if she'd risen from the deep ocean.
---
The air swirled and eddied around them as if they were the rocks within a great and wide riverbed.
---
The air was an anxious swirl of drops, wind-freed from gravity.
---
It is as if the sea air has the ability to whisk my soul into a shared divine space, to lift what would otherwise remain Earthbound toward heavenly skies.
---
The sea air arrives with a nostalgic and humble majesty. Its brine is memories of yesteryear and a promise of days to come.
---
The sea air rises in such lofty drafts to carry heaven's birds ever higher.
---
